{"cursor":"12352","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\nAn 'injunction' is an equitable remedy in the form of a court order that\nrequires a party to do or refrain from doing specific acts. A party that fails\nto comply with an injunction faces criminal or civil penalties and may have to\npay damages or accept sanctions. In some cases, breaches of injunctions are\nconsidered serious criminal offenses that merit arrest and possible prison\nsentences.\n","linknr":249,"url":"Injunction","recorded":1362891907,"links":21,"instances":["law","law"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Equity (law)","Judicial remedies","Legal terms"],"headings":["Rationale and reasons for injunctions","Gag orders (many countries)","American injunctions","Australian apprehended violence orders","{{anchor|UK super-injunctions|UK superinjunction|UK super-injunction}}UK superinjunctions","See also","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f8/Wiktionary-logo-en.svg/37px-Wiktionary-logo-en.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["equity","law"],["standing","law"]],"members":["standing","equity"],"related":["Equitable_remedy","Court_order","Civil_penalty","Trespass","Stalking","Domestic_violence","Harassment","Discrimination","Bullying","Physical_abuse","Sexual_abuse","Real_property","Fraudulent_conveyance","Official_Secrets_Act_1989","Trade_dress","Trademark_infringement","Copyright_infringement","Patent_infringement","Trade_secrets","Tortious","Criminal_contempt","Civil_contempt","Unauthorized_practice_of_law","Gag_order","Preliminary_injunction","Trade_secret","Non-disclosure_agreement","Domestic_violence","Stalking","Sexual_assault","Harassment","Restraining_order","United_States_government","Pullman_Strike","United_States_federal_courts","Trad